  "text": "In light of these observations, we further surveyed the relationship between BCCIP expression and 53BP1 expression in the same set of human breast cancers as presented in Table 1 and a previous report [CITATION_1] . Interestingly, we found a strong correlation between BCCIP negativity and 53BP1 negativity in TNBC, but not in non-TNBC (Table 2 ). This finding is consistent with the notion that loss of 53BP1 is associated with BCCIP deficiency in breast cancer, and indicates a potential synthetic viability relationship between BCCIP and 53BP1 deficiencies.",
